***Introduction***

Our facility is using an 8-hour rotating schedule commonly called The
Southern Swing. This is a pattern that has long since fallen out of
favor with most shiftwork operations; mostly due to the seven days in a
row of work and only one weekend off a month. Shift workers find it
fatiguing and companies find it difficult to hire new people willing to
work such a schedule.

Shiftwork Solutions LLC was called in to show the workforce alternative
ways for covering 24/7. This was done using a survey that was
administered in early January of 2024. The results of that survey showed
a significant amount of interest in a 12-hour rotating pattern commonly
referred to as "The Dupont."

This document is intended to provide comparative information about both,
the current schedule and the Dupont. The goal is to allow the workforce
to choose their preferred option between these two using the information
provided here to help with that decision.

***Schedule Selection Process***

The selection process will involve the workforce reviewing this document
and then turning in the back page to indicate their preference. The
Question and Answers section will cover the agreed upon work and pay
policies that will be used in support of the Dupont schedule, should the
workforce elect to implement it.

Everyone will have a few days to review the contents of this document
before using the last page (Preference Form) to let the company and
union know what you want to do.

