**Appendix A -- Pay Calculations**

Pay is based on your hourly rate and the number of "pay hours" that you
earn. Pay rate times pay hours = total pay. For example, if you make
\$35 an hour and work all 4 weeks of your current schedule (and nothing
else), you will work an average of 42 hours per week and be paid an
average of 43 hours per week. The average weekly check would be 43 x
\$35 = \$1,505.

