**Appendix B -- Vacation Pay Calculations**

[Calculating the Percent Method]{.underline}

To convert pay from weekly to hours, you would divide 2% by 40 hours for
each hour.

.02/40 = .0005 or .05% per hour.

So, if you take 48 hours off, you would get 48 times .05% which comes to
2.4% of the previous year's income. If you take 36 hours off, you would
get 36 times.05% which comes to 1.8% of the previous years income.
Taking 48 hours gets you more money but uses up your vacation faster.

[Calculating the 44 pay hours method]{.underline}

Each hour is paid at 44/40 or 10% extra per hour. So, missing 48 hours
will give you 48 plus 4.8 hours of pay or 52.8 pay hours. Missing 36
hours will give you 36 plus 3.6 hours of pay or 39.6 pay hours.

**Appendix C -- Holiday Time off and Pay Calculations**

[Floating Holidays (7 on Southern Swing and 5 on the
Dupont)]{.underline}

**Southern Swing**: Time off with **7** floating holidays: 7 times 8
hours = **56 hours off work**

> Pay for **7** floating holidays: 7 times 8 hours = **56 hours of pay**

**Dupont:** Time off with **5** floating holidays: 5 times 12 hours =
**60 hours off work**

> Pay for **5** floating holidays: 5 times 12 hours = **60 hours of
> pay**

[Scheduled Holidays (7 total)]{.underline}

**Southern Swing**: You are scheduled to work 75% of the days so you
will work 75% of the scheduled holidays. This comes to 75% times 7
holidays times 8 hours = 42 hours of work on scheduled holidays. Each of
these days has an extra 50% pay so you would make an additional 21 pay
hours from working on a holiday. Additionally, you get 8 hours of pay
for each holiday which is an additional 56 hours of pay. Total
additional income from scheduled holidays is 21 + 56 = **77 pay hours**.

**Dupont:** You are scheduled to work 50% of the days so you will work
50% of the scheduled holidays. This comes to 50% times 7 holidays times
12 hours = 42 hours of work on scheduled holidays. Each of these days
has an extra 50% pay so you would make an additional 21 pay hours from
working on a holiday. Additionally, you get 8 hours of pay for each
holiday which is an additional 56 hours of pay. Total additional income
from scheduled holidays is 21 + 56 = **77 pay hours**

Note: Hours worked on Christmas will continue to be paid at the
double-time rate.

**Appendix D -- Sample Stand-By Policy**

A stand-by policy exists to serve only one purpose -- to ensure that
coverage is available for short notice or no notice absence.

Absences such as vacation or long-term disability are foreseeable and
thus, should be covered using existing policies. However, on a 12-hour
schedule, if someone calls off at the last minute, and no replacement
can be found, then someone ends up working beyond a 12-hour shift which
is considered unsafe and thus, unacceptable.

Here are some guidelines for a typical stand-by policy:

1.  To be on stand-by means that one must be reachable by telephone for
    some time on their day off. Typically, this period extends from 15
    minutes before a shift change to 15 minutes after a shift change.

2.  Since there are 2 shift changes per day, there will be 2 standby
    periods per day.

3.  The person on stand-by cannot be assigned mandatory overtime on the
    day they are on stand-by.

4.  Sufficient numbers should be on standby to ensure a reasonable
    expectation that any short notice absence can be covered. This
    number is typically around one person per 10 people that are
    scheduled off.

5.  The person on stand-by cannot be contacted and called in for any
    purpose other than covering a last-minute absence.

6.  People should be assigned stand-by several weeks in advance.

7.  People on standby should be allowed to trade or simply give up their
    stand-by position to someone else that wants it.

8.  Being on standby is not a paid position. The benefit is that you
    cannot be assigned mandatory overtime on the days you are on
    stand-by. Additionally, the very existence of a stand-by system
    means that not having one does not work and thus, you either have
    such a system or you go to an 8-hour shift schedule.

